"{\"uid\": \"nbcnews.com-news-world-chinese-swimmers-olympics-failed-doping-tests-rcna148701\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"news Alerts There are no new alerts at this time SYDNEY - The world's top anti-doping regulator says 23 Chinese swimmers were cleared to compete at the Tokyo Olympics despite testing positive for a banned heart medication because it agreed with Chinese authorities and ruled that their samples had been contaminated.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 320, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no new alerts\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 35}, {\"ngram\": \"this time\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 48}, {\"ngram\": \"The world's top anti-doping regulator\", \"from\": 58, \"to\": 95}, {\"ngram\": \"23 Chinese swimmers\", \"from\": 101, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned heart medication\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinese authorities\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 264}, {\"ngram\": \"their samples\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The World Anti-Doping Agency said Saturday that the swimmers tested positive for the heart medication trimetazidine in the months leading up to the start of the Tokyo Olympics in 2021 but that Chinese authorities told the agency the positives were the result of contamination.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart medication trimetazidine\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 437}, {\"ngram\": \"the months\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinese authorities\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"the positives\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 564}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Ultimately, we concluded that there was no concrete basis to challenge the asserted contamination,\\\" WADA's senior director of science and medicine Olivier Rabin said in a news release.\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 785, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no concrete basis\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"the asserted contamination\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's senior director\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 723}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 734}, {\"ngram\": \"medicine\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"Olivier Rabin\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"a news release\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 30-member Chinese swim team won six medals in Tokyo, including three golds.\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 837, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999998878593, \"rank\": 1.121171982052442e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 30-member Chinese swim team\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"six medals\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 833}, {\"ngram\": \"three golds\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the athletes still compete for China and are expected to swim at the Paris Olympics this summer.\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 906, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.996348673945708, \"rank\": 0.003664175539482803, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reports about the doping positives came out Saturday in the Daily Telegraph in Sydney and The New York Times.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.999942150444547, \"rank\": 4.386408544586639e-05, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.4468626169697724e-13, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Reports\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 980}, {\"ngram\": \"the doping positives\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"the Daily Telegraph\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA responded to what it called \\\"some misleading and potentially defamatory media coverage this week\\\" and explained the process it undertook upon learning about the positive tests.\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"some misleading and potentially defamatory media coverage\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1212}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The global drug-fighting organization said it also had been given a tip by the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency as early as 2020 - before this case arose - about allegations of doping cover-ups in China but that USADA never followed up with evidence.\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.996348673945708, \"rank\": 0.003664175539482803, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The global drug-fighting organization\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"a tip\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"doping cover-ups\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USADA CEO Travis Tygart called the news of the Chinese positive tests \\\"crushing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1520, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the news\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the Chinese positive tests\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's even more devastating to learn the World Anti-Doping Agency and the Chinese Anti-Doping Agency secretly, until now, swept these positives under the carpet by failing to fairly and evenly follow the global rules that apply to everyone else in the world,\\\" Tygart said.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1853, \"end\": 1859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tygart_Valley_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"the Chinese Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"these positives\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"the carpet\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"the global rules\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Aquatics, which oversees global swimming, told the Daily Telegraph it was confident \\\"that these (adverse analytical findings) were handled diligently and professionally, and in accordance with all applicable anti-doping regulations, including the World Anti-Doping Code.\\\"\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"global swimming\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"the Daily Telegraph\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1939}, {\"ngram\": \"(adverse analytical findings\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"accordance\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"all applicable anti-doping regulations\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Code\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The drug at the center of this case was also the medication that led to the suspension ofRussian figure skater Kamila Valievaat the Winter Olympics in Beijing in 2022.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kamila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2297, \"end\": 2304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.9788149329261817, \"rank\": 0.02156846907518495, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The drug\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2168}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"the medication\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"the suspension\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In that case, WADA moved quickly to sanction Valieva upon learning about her positive test.\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2406, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that case\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2327}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2333}, {\"ngram\": \"sanction\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"her positive test\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The case underscores what many view as a flaw in the global anti-doping system - that a country's own anti-doping organization is often the first line of defense in catching drug cheats and those organizations have different levels of motivation to fulfill that role.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2675, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The case\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2416}, {\"ngram\": \"a flaw\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"the global anti-doping system\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"a country's own anti-doping organization\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"the first line\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"defense\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"drug cheats\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"those organizations\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2617}, {\"ngram\": \"different levels\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2639}, {\"ngram\": \"motivation\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2653}, {\"ngram\": \"that role\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u200e \\u00a9 2025 NBCUniversal Media, LLC\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2707, \"end\": 2710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999997337998038, \"rank\": 2.6620018688533263e-07, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u200e \\u00a9 2025 NBCUniversal Media\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2704}]}]}"